      <section eId="sec_2116">
        <num>2116</num>
        <heading>Additional requirements for applications</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_2116__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>An application\nfor a certificate of title shall be accompanied by the required fee when\nmailed or delivered to the commissioner.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_2116__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Except as provided for in subdivision</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_2116__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of this section, an\napplication for the naming of a lienholder or his assignee on a\ncertificate of title shall be accompanied by the required fee when\nmailed or delivered to the commissioner.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_2116__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The filing of a notice of lien by the office of temporary and\ndisability assistance, or a local social services district, or its\nauthorized representative, or a lien of another state agency operating\nunder title IV-D of the social security act, shall constitute an\napplication for the naming of a lienholder on a certificate of title.\nThe filing of an application by any such agency shall be completed\nwithout payment of a fee.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
